FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE, BOVINE - CHINA: (OIE)
**************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 2 Jan 2006
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Alert Message [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/Messages/060102CHN.htm>

Foot and mouth disease in the People's Republic of China
(Date of previous outbreak of foot and mouth disease in the People's
Republic of China reported to the OIE: May 2005).
Information received on 30 Dec 2005 from Mr Jia Youling, Director
General, Veterinary Bureau, Ministry of Agriculture, Beijing:
Report date: 30 Dec 2005.
An outbreak of foot and mouth disease (FMD) due to virus serotype
Asia1 was reported in ChangQing, JiNan district, ShanDong province.
Date of first confirmation of the event: 29 Dec 2005.
Date of start of the event: 6 Dec 2005.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, post-mortem and laboratory.
Number of animals in the outbreak: 91 (cattle).
Number of cases: 48.
Number of animals destroyed: 91.
Source of outbreak or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive.
Control measures undertaken:
-stamping out;
-quarantine;
-movement control inside the country;
-screening;
-zoning;
-vaccination;
-disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s);
-dipping/spraying.
OIE Animal Health Information Department
<information.dept@oie.int>
Further details will be published in the next issue of weekly Disease
Information, available on line as from Thursday 5 Jan 2006, in the
afternoon (GMT).
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The location of this outbreak is inland near the Huang He (Yellow)
river in Shandong province. This province is in northeast China,
across the Yellow Sea from Korea. We will await news of FMD activity
in other regions of China where there were outbreaks in 2005. -
Mod.PC]
